b'[![](../../cdshop/cdinfo.jpg)](../../cdshop/index.htm)  \n[Sacred Texts](../../index.htm)  [Hinduism](../index.htm)  [Index](index.htm)\n[Previous](av107.htm)  [Next](av109.htm)\n\n* * *\n\n## VI, 81. A bracelet as an amulet to ensure conception.\n\n1\\. A holder art thou, holdest both hands, drivest off the Rakshas. An\nacquirer of offspring and wealth this bracelet hath become!  \n2\\. O bracelet, open up the womb, that the embryo be put (into it)! Do thou, O\nlimit (-setting bracelet), furnish a son, bring him here (A gamaya), thou that\ncomest here (Agame)!  \n3\\. The bracelet that Aditi wore, when she desired a son.Tvashtar shall fasten\nupon this woman, intending that she shall beget a son.\n\n* * *\n\n[Next: III, 23. Charm for obtaining a son (pumsavanam)](av109.htm)\n\n'